news.title: Greystar to invest $1.53 billion in European real estate market in 2024
news.para: The market has and continues to reprice and investors were extending and pretending and now more people are willing to sell in order to reallocate the capital," Mark Allnutt said on the sidelines of the MIPIM real estate industry gathering in Cannes this week.

news.title: European parliament approves law to make buildings more energy efficient
news.para: A majority of 370 members of the European Parliament voted in favour of the bill, while 199 opposed and 46 abstained.

news.title: Suvidha kendras in Ludhiana to remain open on holidays till March 31
news.para: These centres will remain operational on March 16 (Saturday), March 23 (Saturday), March 29 (Good Friday), March 30 (Saturday), and March 31 (Sunday), It has also been decided to keep the suvidha kendras open till 4pm till the month end.

news.title: Ludhiana development body partially razes unauthorised colony
news.para: Glada’s demolition drive was strongly opposed by the locals at the site on account of their recently applied NoCs for their plots/buildings.

news.title: Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar civic body to issue unique digital door number plates to properties
news.para: Speaking at the launch of the initiative in the Garkheda area, deputy municipal commissioner Aprna Thete said each number plate will have a QR code.

news.title: Residents from merged areas protest against Pune civic body over high property tax
news.para: Residents of Uttamnagar, Shivane, Kondhwe and Kopre villages participated in the rally that converged at Shivane ward office. “The tax charged from residents is more than what we paid when we were under the grampanchyat.

news.title: VDA unveils revised Master Plan-2031
news.para: Highlighting the contents of the revised masterplan VDA’s city planner Prabhat Kumar said that restrictions on construction work in Sarnath area had been relaxed following consultation with the Archaeological Survey of India and other departments concerned.

news.title: Over 2.5 lakh houses allotted to beneficiaries in Uttar Pradesh till 2023-24
news.para: Launched on Feb 2, 2018, a staggering 2.57 lakh houses have been allotted to beneficiaries under the scheme till 2023-24, underscoring the govt's unwavering commitment to uplift the underprivileged.

news.title: Delhi civic body seals eight properties of tax defaulters in Shahdara south zone
news.para: The MCD will take strict action against defaulters of property tax in various wards. To avoid such action, property taxpayers are advised to pay their outstanding property tax by March 31, 2024, the civic body said in a statement.

news.title: Union cabinet likely to approve two more Delhi Metro corridors on March 13
news.para: Sources were tight lipped about the cost of these stretches under the DMRC Phase-IV, which will provide direct connectivity. While the 8-km long Lajpat Nagar-Saket G Block corridor will have eight stations, the 12-km Inderlok-Indraprastha line will have 10 stations.

news.title: Nexus Select aims to double portfolio in five years with acquisition-led strategy
news.para: Blackstone-backed Nexus Select Trust plans to double its assets portfolio to 20 million sq ft in 5 years. CEO Dalip Sehgal stated that the trust can borrow $1 billion or swap units for assets to fund acquisitions. The trust currently owns 17 malls across 14 cities, including Ahmedabad and Amritsar.

news.title: Property registrations up 64% year-on-year in Kolkata in February 2024
news.para: The bouncing back of sales in the affordable home sector has contributed significantly to this growth. While there was a time lag between property sales and registrations earlier, they happen almost simultaneously now to avail of the 2% stamp duty cut benefit.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to offer 15% rebate on property tax dues till March 31
news.para: According to norms, those who fail to clear property tax in time have to pay interest at a rate of 18% per annum. The civic body also carries out sealing drives and auctions properties of those who have not paid property tax for a long time.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body hikes commercial properties rates, approves Wave City plan
news.para: The reserve price of GDA’s commercial properties in Indirapuram was Rs 1.5 lakh/sqm. After the hike, it will become Rs 1,58,700/sqm.

news.title: Shree Cement purchases five ready-mix cement plants in Mumbai for Rs 33.50 crore
news.para: These RMC plants have an aggregate capacity of 422 CUM/hour and have been acquired by Shree Cement at an aggregate consideration of Rs 33.50 crore.

news.title: UK: Persimmon's pretax profit dips 52% to $450.5 million in 2023
news.para: Shares in the FTSE 100 firm slipped more than 3% to 1,328 pence in early trading, the biggest decliner on the blue-chip index in percentage terms.

news.title: Germany's TAG Immobilien posts net loss of 410.9 million euros in 2023
news.para: The loss followed further writedowns in the value of its property holdings, and the company said it would suspend dividend payments for the second consecutive year to strengthen its capital position.

news.title: South Korea's land minister bearish on property as population ages
news.para: South Korea's land minister says the country won't see a repeat of the sharp home price gains as its population rapidly ages and economy slows. The minister vows to promote public rental accommodation to improve access to housing. .

news.title: China's first two consumption-related REITs close roughly flat on debut
news.para: The two real estate investment trusts listed in Shanghai are backed by shopping centres owned by developer China Jinmao and supermarkets owned by retailer Wumart.

news.title: China Vanke's bonds eased after Moody's starts ratings review
news.para: Vanke's Hong Kong-listed shares opened down 1%, though they strengthened to climbed 1.4% as of 0229 GMT, while its Shenzhen-listed shares dropped 0.4%.
